places.name: East Swanson Dock Sidings (SWD)
places.desc:
Part of the East Swanson Dock intermodal Terminal. 
Patrick Terminal sidings.
Two dual gauge 620m sidings.

places.name: Southern Cross Layby Sidings
places.desc: Two sidings near Southern Cross Station. These two sidings host two 6 car trains for the Burnley Group when they are not required.

places.name: Jacana flyover
places.desc: Where the North East standard gauge line crosses over the suburban tracks, and the Albion-Jacana broad gauge tracks diverge

places.name: Swanson Dock Link Line
places.desc: Dual gauge link line connecting the Swanson Dock complex to Appleton Dock.

places.name: North Melbourne Rail Viewing Platform
places.desc: Platform that provides views across North Melbourne Station and Southern Cross Station. great Views of V/Line & standard gauge trains using the flyover.

places.name: Broadmeadows Siding A
places.desc: Rarely used due to its short length (max 3 EMU cars), but occasionally defective railcars or locomotives are stowed here.

places.name: Tottenham (TLS).
places.desc:
Location: 8.7km by Rail from Spencer St.
Length: 2900m.

places.name: V/Line, South Dynon Fuel Point.
places.desc: V/Line Locomotives are Fueled here, Rollingstock is also Provisioned here.

places.name: UGL Rail, Spotswood (GLM).
places.desc: Heavy maintenance facility for Pacific National's SG Fleet.

places.name: North Melbourne Stabling Sidings
places.desc: This yard stores trains whilst they are not in use. It has a capacity of eight 6 car electric sets.

places.name: Footscray Road Sidings (SWD)
places.desc:
Part of the East Swanson Dock Intermodal Terminal.
Common User sidings.
Two dual gauge 563m sidings.

places.name: South Dynon SG Turntable (SDY).
places.desc:
SG turntable in South Dynon.
Currently booked out.

places.name: Jacana Loop
places.desc:
Distance: 26.789km from Southern Cross (via Albion)
Crossing loop for BG trains on the Albion-Jacana goods line.
Length: ~850m

places.name: Melbourne Operations Terminal (MOP).
places.desc: Formerly used for PN Steel train provisioning, now used for wagon storage.

places.name: Albion Curve
places.desc: Popular Photography Location - Good for Up Trains in the early morning and late afternoon/evening. Good for Down Trains in The afternoon/evening.

places.name: West Footscray gauge splitter
places.desc: The gauge splitter for broad and standard gauge on the goods lines near West Footscray station

places.name: Brooklyn Jct. (BNS)
places.desc: Junction of the Broad and Standard Gauge Lines.

places.name: QUBE, Altona (CRT).
places.desc: QUBE S/G Maintenance and Wagon Storage Yard.

places.name: Glenroy Bank
places.desc: 1 in 50 gradient for down trains heading to Seymour.

places.name: Pacific National Wagon Maintenance Centre (WMC).
places.desc: Pacific National's Melbourne Wagon Maintenance Centre. Both B/G & S/G Wagons are maintained here.

places.name: ANZAC Siding, Spotswood
places.desc: Used to load and unload SSR and PN rail trains. It has both SG and BG access. Also used to store track maintenance vehicles

places.name: Laverton (LAV).
places.desc:
Location: 19.0km by Rail from Spencer St.
Length: 1846m.
SCT, Laverton entrance off of the Loop.

places.name: SCT, Laverton (SCT)
places.desc:
SCT's Melbourne Hub for Intermodal services to Adelaide and Perth (AM9/MA9 & MP9/PM9), Brisbane (MB9/BM9) as well as Sadleirs Transfers to Spotswood as 770*V and Steel Transfers to North Dynon as 7942V/9743V.

The terminal includes a large container hardstand and warehouse for the loading of Louvre vans. The expansion of the yard to the east allows services coming in from the east to access the terminal without changing direction.

places.name: McIntyre Loop & Siding (MSG)
places.desc:
Location: 16.0km by rail from Southern Cross.
Crossing loop and through siding.
Both are 892m in length - however crosses at this location are rare owing to the short length of the loop and the proximity of the lengthy Tullamarine Passing Lane.

places.name: Allied Mills, Kensington.
places.desc: Allied Mills Flour Mill, Kensington is serviced by SSR Broad Gauge Grain Trains.

places.name: South Dynon Broad Gauge Turntable (SDB).
places.desc: Turntable for Broad Gauge Locomotives in Melbourne.

places.name: Newport Workshops West Block (NSR).
places.desc: Home of Steamrail Victoria, 707 Operations and DERMPAV. Also where plenty of carriages/locomotives were built for the Victorian Railways

places.name: Agents Siding - North Dynon (NDA).
places.desc:
Tracks No. 11 - No. 16 of North Dynon.

Sheet Steel unloading area (track 11)

Used to store wagons awaiting maintenance. 
Used by QUBE and PN.
Aurizon also uses it for stabling wagons between services.

places.name: Newport Workshops East Block
places.desc: Mainly a storage area for VDOT, Metro and V/Line

places.name: Newport Station (NPT)
places.desc:
Distance: 10.555km from Southern Cross
Junction for the Werribee Line from the Williamstown line. Metro services travelling in any direction can terminate here.

At certain times, three car Williamstown shuttle services operate to Newport and terminate, using one of the two sidings to the North to turn around.

One of those sidings also provides BG access to the DG Sunshine-Newport freight line, which allows BG traffic to access Newport Workshops from the freight line. The freight line remains DG past the station, before the BG diverges into a short holding track and eventually joins the mainline towards Geelong.

places.name: Appleton Dock Grain Terminal
places.desc:
Bulk Grain Terminal now operated by Louis Dreyfus Companies (Previously Emerald Grain).

Main Operator is SSR with grain sourced from Southern NSW, and Victorian SG & BG lines. PN also operate the occasional train to this facility.

Lengths
580m - #1 Road
550m - #2 Road
350m - Unloading Road.

places.name: Sadleirs Logistics Siding, Spotswood (NPS).
places.desc:
Melbourne depot. Shunt trip runs to and from SCT, Laverton.
Louvre Vans and some containers transhipped off services to/from Sydney and Perth.
Rail Operator - SCT
Train Number - Dedicated 770*V or sometimes combined with 7942V/9743V Steel transfers.

places.name: Broadmeadows Stabling Siding
places.desc: Used to stable 3 six carriage Cragieburn Line EMUs when they are not in use.

places.name: Locomotive Provisioning Centre (LPC).
places.desc: PN Intermodal Locomotives stable here after arriving into Melbourne before provisioning and stabling prior to departing on their next service.

places.name: North Melbourne Arrivals Yard
places.desc: North Melbourne arrivals, which is used by all BG freight operators for various purposes, such as SSR for running around locos from Kensington to Tottenham Yard. Diverted PN Freight for Tocumwal also uses this yard.

places.name: Southern Cross Station (SSS)
places.desc:
Departure or Arrival point for just about all V/Line services.
Platforms 1-7 are dead end platforms used by V/Line.

Platform 8 is normally used by V/Line, however Metro services to Flemington Racecourse Line use it during special events. Platform 8 South also has overhead power, but it is not currently available for use.
Platform 1 & 2 are dual gauge, used by SG passenger services to Albury, Sydney and Adelaide.
9-14 are suburban through platforms.
15-16 are through country platforms used by select Geelong, Ballarat and Bendigo services to avoid the North Melbourne Flyover. All Traralgon services also use these platforms.

This station also marks "0km" for the entire Victorian railway network.

places.name: Albion (Broad Gauge).
places.desc:
Location: 14.5km by rail from Spencer St.
Length: 1000m.
Melbourne-bound broad gauge trains are often held here to await a path on the suburban tracks towards Tottenham.

places.name: Ardern Street Sidings
places.desc: Two unelectrified sidings adjacent to the Metro Trains Melbourne light maintenance facility at Macaulay. One 6 carriage Vlocity  set is stabled here during the off-peak period.

places.name: GemCo Rail Workshop (SDC).
places.desc: GemCo Rail is an Independent Locomotive and Rolling Stock Maintenance contractor, providing cyclical maintenance and overhaul of locomotives, passenger cars, wagons, as well as track maintenance equipment. At their South Dynon location, they maintain PN's BG and SG fleet and QUBE's BG fleet and V/Line N class locomotives as required.

places.name: Flemington Racecourse Station (RCE)
places.desc:
The terminus of the line of the same name. It is only used by revenue services during special events or disruptions, which trains terminate at either Showgrounds or this station. Services on the line usually run to Southern Cross Platform 8 and terminate. 

During the Melbourne Cup, services can be as regular as every four minutes. Outside of special events, the line is used by empty trains heading here for stabling. It has a capacity of at least eight 6 car EMU sets.

places.name: McConnell Dowell Sunshine North
places.desc:
Location: 16.0km by Rail from Spencer St.
Used for rail trains, storing of track maintenance equipment, stabling of rail grinders and others. It has both BG and SG access. Wagons can also be gauge converted here.

places.name: Alstom, South Dynon Maintenance Centre
places.desc:
Dual Gauge workshop where maintenance is carried out on V/Line's BG and SG fleet. Includes a wheel lathe, one of only two Broad Gauge wheel lathes in Victoria (the other one is at Newport Workshops).

The southern end of this building was formerly used by PN (and later Downer EDi when PN began contracting out locomotive maintenance), however they vacated the building  in 2016. PN's Victorian SG locomotives are now maintained in UGL Spotswood and BG locomotives are maintained at the North Bendigo Workshops (BRW).

places.name: Alstom Carriage Workshops, West Melbourne (Southern Cross)
places.desc: V/Line's main train maintenance facility. Located adjacent to the Dudley Street sidings and near Southern Cross station. Vlocities, Sprinters and Carriages are maintained here.

places.name: Metro, North Melbourne Yard
places.desc: Yard that can stable eight 6 car EMUs. Used to stable trains when they are not in use.

places.name: work place
places.desc: Snr Leading Shunter Bank Sidings

places.name: Metro Infrastructure Works Siding, Paisley
places.desc:
Distance: 13.500km from Southern Cross
BG SSR maintenance trains are loaded here.
Length: ~180m with run around loop and headshunt.

places.name: Sunshine North Pedestrian Crossing
places.desc: Good spot for Up trains in afternoon and evening.

places.name: Metro Tunnel Western Portal
places.desc: Where the Metro Tunnel will begin on the western side, scheduled for completion in 2025.

places.name: Westona (WTO)
places.desc:
Distance: 18.533km from Southern Cross.
A portmanteau of ‘West’ and ‘Altona’, this station was opened in January 1985 as part of the extension of the Altona Line to Laverton, forming the Altona Loop. Today it forms an important crossing loop on the Altona Loop line.

places.name: North Melbourne Flyover
places.desc: Used on V/Line, JBR and XPT services to cross the suburban tracks, to get to platforms 1-8 at Southern Cross. Both tracks are dual-gauge. It has a speed limit of 30kph.

places.name: Tottenham Junction (TBS).
places.desc: Tottenham Junction is the triangle junction where trains can either head to Adelaide, Sydney or Melbourne. The western north-south leg was finished in 2010, allowing trains to completely bypass Melbourne.

places.name: North Dynon Jct. (WBJ).
places.desc: Used for all QUBE services. Also for SSR grain wagon transfers and all BG LE's to Tottenham if coming from South Kensington.

places.name: Macaulay Light Maintenance Centre
places.desc: Opened in the 1990s to help replace the Jolimont yards, this sees light maintenance of the MTM fleet. It also contains a few storage sidings.

places.name: Gowanbrae Viduct
places.desc: Nice shot of Up BG & SG Trains going over the viaduct in the afternoon, not bad for morning down trains.

places.name: West Swanson Dock Siding (SWD)
places.desc:
Part of the West Swanson Dock Intermodal Terminal, operated DP World. 
One dual gauge 560m siding servicing a hardstand.

places.name: Appleton Dock (APD)
places.desc:
Intermodal Receival Point for AFCS Port Logistics (formally Patricks) for the Port of Melbourne. 

Yard includes 3 Common User Sidings, and 2 ACFS transshipping sidings.

PN is the primary operator for services to and from Warrnambool, Tocumwal, Merbein and Griffith.

SCT's Service from Dooen is currently using this facility whilst Westgate Tunnel works obstruct Swanson Dock.

Lengths
1010m - #3 Road (Run-a-round Road)
1000m - #4 Road, Common User
910m - #5 Road, Common User
668m - #6 Road, AFCS
666m - #7 Road, AFCS
520m - Wharf Head Shunt

places.name: Bunbury Street Tunnel & Bridge
places.desc: Popular photography location, entrance for most freight into the Port of Melbourne. As well as Entry into the Melbourne Freight Terminal and North Dynon. Also for all standard gauge passenger trains.

places.name: Sydenham Yard
places.desc: Holds up to six 7 carriage HCMTs when they are not in use, two 560m sidings.

places.name: South Dynon Fuel Point.
places.desc: Pacific National Bulk, SSR and V/Line locomotives are fueled here.

places.name: Metro, Newport Yards (NPS)
places.desc: Used for stabling all Metro EMUs for the Werribee and Williamstown lines, with a capacity of 15 six carriage sets.

places.name: Somerville Rd Brooklyn
places.desc: Nice shot for up trains in both morning and afternoon.

places.name: Fulton Hogan, Brooklyn Siding.
places.desc:
Where the aggregates train from Kilmore East operated by QUBE is unloaded. 
Train Designation - 9341/9342 and 9345/9346

places.name: Footscray Station (FSY)
places.desc:
Distance: 5.623km from Southern Cross.
A major "junction" station (though no physical junctions between lines are actually located here) between the Newport lines, and the lines toward Sunshine. 

Platforms 1 & 2 are used by Sunbury services. 
Platforms 3 & 4 are unelectrified and used by all V/Line services towards Geelong, Ballarat and Bendigo. They pick up/set down only depending on their direction of travel. 
Platforms 5 & 6 are used by Cross City group trains which operate between Frankston and Williamstown/Werribee.

places.name: Brooklyn Up Trainspotting
places.desc: A nice photography spot nestled in some trees. Zoom lens required. Best in the afternoon. There is also alternatively a ballast pile nearby.

places.name: Kernot St Spotswood
places.desc: A popular location for photography. There are spots available for any time of day.

places.name: V/Line, North Melbourne Arrivals Yard
places.desc: Used by V/Line for storage of Vlocity DMUs when not in use. V/Line loco hauled empty car runs to South Kensington for loco run-arounds also pass through here.

places.name: Geelong Rd Brooklyn
places.desc: A nice elevated shot for morning down trains. To access, climb up the embankment on the side of the road. Better shot while standing on the thin platform on Geelong Rd, just watch out for cars.

places.name: Francis St Brooklyn
places.desc: Good for up trains from mid morning to sunset, just stay on sun side. Too much obstruction for morning down trains. West side of Xing could work for down trains on cloudy days

places.name: Melbourne Freight & Steel Terminals (MFT)(MST).
places.desc:
Pacific National open access yard. This is PN's intermodal facility in Melbourne. It has both Standard and Broad Gauge access.

Intermodal services to and from Perth (MP2, MP4, MP5/PM5, PM6, MP7/PM7), Adelaide (MA5/AM5), Sydney (MS2/SM2) and Brisbane (MB5, MB/BM4) depart from here.

PN steel services for Infrabuild also arrive and depart from here, to/from Port Augusta/Whyalla and Perth (XM4 and MP2/PM4 respectively).

places.name: Albion Station
places.desc: Popular photography location for those who don't care about sun conditions. The south end of the platform in the afternoon isn't too bad but it is quite easy to just walk up St Albans Rd and see the train at the curve.

places.name: Broadmeadows Station (BMS/BRQ).
places.desc:
Location: 17.0km by rail from Spencer St.

Terminus for a small amount of peak Cragieburn line services. All Seymour and Shepparton line services stop here.

It also has a third platform on the standard gauge track which is serviced by the XPT and Albury line services.

places.name: North Dynon Yard (NDY)
places.desc:
VicTrack Open Access Yard, operated in partnership with QUBE Logistics and Aurizon.

QUBE uses this yard for their Steel workings with WM7/MW7 trains to Port Kembla and for at least two daily trains to/from Long Island. The Maryvale also stages here.

Aurizon uses this yard on their thrice weekly MB1/BM1 intermodal services to/from Glenlee (Sydney) and Fisherman Island (Brisbane), and for four weekly Intermodal services to Adelaide/Perth (MP1/PM1), as well as a once weekly 5XM1/6MX1 service to Port Pirie which connects with 6SP1/3PS1.

SCT also operate Steel Transfers to/from Laverton as 7942V/9743V which are attached to SCT's Intermodal services to Adelaide and Perth.

places.name: Laverton Station (LAV)
places.desc:
Distance: 21.005km (express line)
22.180 km via Altona Loop line
The terminus for local Altona Loop services on weekdays, with Werribee services using the express line. Weekend Werribee services run via the loop and stop all stations. Terminating trains coming from the city can use any platform, however generally only platform 3 is used for those that have come via Altona.

places.name: Flinders Street Railway Station (FSS)
places.desc: An icon of Melbourne, it is the focal point of all of Melbourne's Suburban rail services. All lines arrive/depart from this station, barring the Williamstown line at certain times and the Alamein line in the off peak. This is Melbourne's busiest railway station. There are 14 platforms, although only 12 are in use (Platform 11 & 14 are closed).

places.name: Victoria Dock (Westgate Sidings) (VDK/WGS).
places.desc:
The QUBE Ultima Containers (917*) departs from here.
QUBE's Maryvale Paper Train (9475/9476) also operates in and out of here, before the containers are trucked to DP World near Swanson Dock.
Lengths: 
621m - #1 Road
617m - #2 Road
665m - #3 Road
All tracks are dual gauge.

places.name: W-Track
places.desc:
Eastern leg of the Dynon Triangle.

Used predominantly by freight operators to access North & South Dock Lines or South Dynon from North Dynon. Also, by freight operators to turn locomotives as required.

places.name: Downer, Newport (NPW).
places.desc:
Workshop mainly used to perform Heavy Maintenance on  Metro's Fleet & V/line's Locomotives - broad gauge access only.
Also, sees other operator's locomotives pass through as required to use the wheel lathe.

places.name: Watergardens (Sydenham) (SDM)
places.desc:
Distance: 23.176km from Southern Cross.
Platform 1 - through city-bound services.
Platform 2 - terminating services from the city. Every second service terminates here.
Platform 3 - down services.

All Metro services stop here, as well as all Swan Hill trains. However, only a select few other V/Line services stop here in peak hours. 

Trains can use any platform to terminate in the down direction, however for platform 3 doing so requires a shunt to either side of the station to change into plaftorm 2. Platform 2 can be accessed from any direction including the sidings and vice versa. Platform 1 on the down can only access the sidings. On the up, trains can terminate on platform 2 only.

The station was originally supposed to be named Sydenham after one of the suburbs it serves, hence its code. The name is also printed into the brickwork of the station building. However, naming rights were sold to the adjacent Watergardens Shopping Centre.

places.name: Sunshine Station (SUN)
places.desc:
Distance: 12.254km from Southern Cross.
A major station served by Sunbury metropolitan services, as well as V/Line services from the Ballarat and Geelong lines. Bendigo services also run through the station, and the North East SG runs past. The Geelong and Ballarat lines diverge past here, forming the end of dedicated RRL trackage for the Bendigo Line.

Trains in both directions, for both V/Line and Metro services, can terminate here if required.

Platforms 1 & 2 are used by Sunbury Line trains.
Platforms 3 & 4 are used by most services on the Geelong and Ballarat Lines, which pick up/set down only depending on their direction of travel. Freight services accessing or coming from Tottenham Yard use the tracks through Platforms 1 & 2; those accessing or coming from the line to Newport travel through 3 & 4.

places.name: Deer Park Junction (DPW)
places.desc:
Distance: 19.350km from Southern Cross.
Deer Park Junction is the point where the RRL (Geelong line) splits away from the Ballarat Line.

places.name: Southern Cross Bank Sidings (BKS)
places.desc: Where Swan Hill trains are marshalled from the yards for shunting into Southern Cross for service. Also where other trains stable between services.

places.name: Calder Park Yard (CPV)
places.desc:
Distance: 26.420km from Southern Cross.

This yard currently has space for roughly twenty-four  6 carriage EMU sets (October '22), however this will be expanded and a light maintenance facility will be constructed for the servicing of HCMT sets from 2025.

places.name: Southern Cross Car Sidings (SCC)
places.desc: Sprinter and Vlocity DMU's are stabled here when not in use.

places.name: Passing Lane 1 Tullamarine (TSG).
places.desc:
Location - 22.3km by rail from Southern Cross.
Length - 6059m. 
The loop track is dual gauge.

places.name: Tottenham Broad Gauge Yard (TYD)
places.desc:
Large yard used as the base of SSR's Broad Gauge grain operations, with services from country Victoria arriving here before shuttles are run to Appleton Dock and Kensington to unload.

SSR also uses this yard for short term wagon storage for works trains and other services. PN uses this yard mainly for wagon storage, but also to stage services as required. QUBE occasionally stores wagons here.

All Broad Gauge services heading west out of Dynon must travel through/past this yard.

places.name: North Dynon Fuel Point
places.desc:
Used by QUBE and Aurizon (and on the Rare Occasion, SSR & EV120) for fueling and provisioning of locos, as well as stabling of locos when not required. Has both BG and SG access.

1 Pump Track (Commonly Called Broad Gauge Fuel Point)  - BG 
2 & 3 Pump Track - SG. 2 Pump is Usually Occupied by the Aurizon PM/MP Locos
2 pump road is connected with the Agents Sidings/11 Road.
3 pump is in the middle of the two and is where the WM/MW7 & Aurizon's Brisbane Locos stable/fuel.

Lengths: 
1 & 3 Pump Road(s) are both 70m Long Concrete Pads. With Additional Room outside the Pad.
2 Pump Road has a 45m long pad with no Additional Room due to it being Situated on 11 track.

places.name: Essendon Station (ESD)
places.desc:
Distance: 8.007km from Southern Cross.

Major station on the Cragieburn line, featuring three platforms, however Platform 1 is not regularly used as it is too short for a 6 car EMU. It features intermediate terminating facilities for trains in both directions.

A limited number of V/Line Seymour line services stop here.

places.name: West Footscray Station (WFY)
places.desc:
Distance: 7.325km from Southern Cross

West Footscray station situated between Middle Footscray and Tottenham provides a great view of Tottenham Yard. The footbridge also produces some good photos of down and up freight trains on SG and BG.

The station features three platforms - Platform 1 used by through citybound services,
Platform 2 is currently out of use however it will be used by terminating services from the Dandenong corridor once the Metro Tunnel opens.
Platform 3 is used by down services towards Watergardens and Sunbury.

West Footscray will form the Western end of the CBTC high capacity signalling system.
